# flotilla private denylist — TEMPLATE
#
# Copy this file to  .flotilla/private-denylist  (which is gitignored) and fill
# it with the identifiers that are specific to YOUR deployment — the names that
# should never appear in a public artifact (code, tests, docs, issues, PRs).
# The boundary guard (scripts/check-private-boundary.sh) reads it and fails CI on
# a hit. In CI, provide the same content via the FLOTILLA_PRIVATE_DENYLIST repo
# secret instead, so your list is never committed.
#
# One term or regex per line (the static guard matches with `grep -P`; the runtime
# firewall matches with Go RE2). Keep terms to the RE2-compatible subset — NO lookahead
# or backreferences — because the runtime firewall compiles this list at `flotilla
# watch` / `notify` startup and a non-RE2 construct is a FATAL boot error (fail-closed,
# never a silently-skipped term). Matching is multi-line (anchors are per-line) and
# CASE-SENSITIVE (enumerate case variants, or alternate them). Blank lines and
# #-comments are ignored.
# Keep it HIGH-SIGNAL: tokens with no legitimate generic use, so the guard never
# flaps. Ambiguous words (a common noun that doubles as a desk name) are better
# caught by review against docs/private-public-boundary.md than by this list.
#
# The lines below are ILLUSTRATIVE placeholders — replace them with your own.

# --- your desk / agent names (the real ones, not the generic xo/backend/...) ---
your-xo-name
your-worker-desk-name

# --- your org / venture / project names ---
YourOrgName
YourVentureName

# --- your broker / data vendor / external services ---
YourBrokerName
YourDataVendor

# --- your account-id shapes (regex) ---
# ACCT[0-9]{6,}
